
  Usage: slc
    slc [options] [command] [args]
    slc <npm-command> [npm-command-args]
    slc <script-file> [args]

  Commands:

    npm                    run a npm command - [npm] <npm-command> [npm-command-args]
    run                    run a specified script - [run] <script-file> [args]
    env                    print node environment information
    version                print node version
    help [command]         print usage info for [command]
    debug                  debug a script
    create                 generate modules and applications

  Options:

    -h, --help  output usage information

  Note that npm and run are optional if the npm-command name or script-file
  doesn't conflict with other slc commands.

  Examples:

    $ slc create web mywebapp
    $ slc run app.js
    $ slc npm list
    $ slc npm install -f express
    Same as above, but omitting optional "npm":
    $ slc install -f express
